data.title: Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan: The Voice Of Pakistan
data.meta_description: With his intense stage presence and relentless drive to improve, Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan single-handedly brought Qawwali, a form of Sufi devotional music, to the West and the non-Muslim world. In the process, he influenced an unlikely array of music around the world.
